caption: One of many hidden gardens in paris, this one is quite small, however very pretty with plenty of seating, its well located in the Marais, and not as popular as you would expect
Beautiful small park/garden very well maintained. There are several benches to sit and relax.
Very private. A hidden gem... Not sure if you can get sunlight as it's surrounded by buildings.
Tranquil place - the tulips were out
Very quiet garden, great place to reflect or read.
Small well groomed garden. Very private. Only open 10-6. Good place to take a load off your feet.

A magnificent French garden, quite secret and out of sight in the marsh.  It is calm and relaxing, uncrowded and very pleasant.  Far from the hustle and bustle of the Marais, it is perfect for relaxing with a good free lunch and having lunch outdoors.  Quite in the shade, it is particularly pleasant to go there in summer to find a little freshness.  Pay attention to the times, it closes quite early.

Very pretty, quiet and uncrowded garden unlike its opposite. Designed in the French style, the layout of this 1575 garden highlights the elegant lines of the hotel Méderic Donon (son-in-law of the sculptor Giacomo della Robbia) Today Conacq museum Jay founder of the La Samaritaine stores.
Wonderful little relaxation area in the middle of the Marais. Very quiet, for a reading, a sandwich, a break. Well maintained. Limited opening hours.
Delighted to find this little garden empty, while the neighboring square is full. Benches in the shade to eat my sandwich! A little noise from the neighboring school. Backed by the Cognacq-Jay museum
Dirty, dilapidated, stoners, alcohol drinkers when smoking or drinking is normally prohibited. The Town Hall does nothing even though it is normally a garden for CHILDREN
Rikiki garden and pretty plantations but in the shade in summer.
Very small square, very pretty, rectangular and wedged in the middle of old buildings like a jewel in its historic setting.... A haven of tranquility which the day I passed there was deserted....
On rue de Francs Bourgeois in the heart of the Marais district, come and relax in this small garden, sheltered from the noise but always sunny.
Very good garden Very discreet
08/2017: A garden hidden behind bars and a hedge but which is accessible. Beautiful home surrounding this peaceful garden
Hidden from most people is this small but lovely garden in the Marais
Amazing little green space that you don't dare enter. Pleasant for a little quiet break.
A beautiful and quiet corner for a moment of rest in the historic center of Paris.
Small garden, barely visible but really small
A pleasant little corner of calm in the hustle and bustle of Paris.
Not bad
Little hidden gem in the passage, calm and inspiring.
Flowery and very quiet garden
beautiful park
